<subSubSection id="95E929FBA13EFF81FF18FD87FE8CCE1E" pageId="4" pageNumber="365" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DD4C7A70A13EFF81FF18FD87FE8CCE1E" blockId="4.[151,1437,333,612]" pageId="4" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="EF87A662A13EFF81FF18FD87FE91CE61" bold="true" box="[199,322,513,540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="365">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Robust fly with dense erect setal pile giving a bumble bee-like appearance; head with black setal pile, thorax, abdomen and legs with yellow pile, end of abdomen with black setal pile; wing hyaline, smoky infuscate in distal half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
